metadata.name: TUBE'S MOODS
metadata.description:
Tube's moods from baker street station.

Baker Street is a London Underground station at the junction of Baker Street and the Marylebone Road in the City of Westminster. It is one of the original stations of the Metropolitan Railway, the world's first underground railway.

Picture information :
Camera : LEICA M-E (TYP 240)
Lens : Leica 35mm f/2 Summicron v3 
Jpeg : 6000x4000 Pixel : Resolution 300 dpi
Location : Baker Street Station / United Kingdom
